nt":[]}},{"type":"link","title":null,"url":"https://github.com/adam-mcdaniel/free","children":[{"type":"text","value":"free","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":411,"offset":526},"end":{"line":7,"column":415,"offset":530},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":410,"offset":525},"end":{"line":7,"column":455,"offset":570},"indent":[]},"data":{"hProperties":{"target":"_blank","rel":"nofollow noopener noreferrer"}}},{"type":"text","value":". It used a super-set of Brain**** with 3 new instructions for dynamic memory management. After a substantial amount of keyboard clacking and lots of confusion, I had accidentally made a working compiler! The end result looked like this:","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":455,"offset":570},"end":{"line":7,"column":692,"offset":807},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1,"offset":116},"end":{"line":7,"column":692,"offset":807},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"image","title":null,"url":"/blog/media/free.png","alt":"Free Code","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1,"offset":809},"end":{"line":9,"column":35,"offset":843},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1,"offset":809},"end":{"line":9,"column":35,"offset":843},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"I couldn’t believed it worked; it was incredible. The only problem was that ","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1,"offset":845},"end":{"line":11,"column":77,"offset":921},"indent":[]}},{"type":"emphasis","children":[{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"free was absolute garbage","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":80,"offset":924},"end":{"line":11,"column":105,"offset":949},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":78,"offset":922},"end":{"line":11,"column":107,"offset":951},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":77,"offset":921},"end":{"line":11,"column":108,"offset":952},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":". It couldn’t be used for anything. At all. There wasn’t a type system, memory was basically impossible to manage, there wasn’t any kind of IO other than STDIN and STDOUT, there was no error checking system of any kind, etc. I loved my creation, but it wasn’t practical.","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":108,"offset":952},"end":{"line":11,"column":378,"offset":1222},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1,"offset":845},"end":{"line":11,"column":378,"offset":1222},"indent":[]}},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"children":[{"type":"link","url":"#oaks-conception","title":null,"children":[],"data":{"hProperties":{"aria-label":"oaks conception permalink","class":"anchor before"},"hChildren":[{"type":"raw","value":"<svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg>"}]}},{"type":"text","value":"Oak’s Conception","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":4,"offset":1227},"end":{"line":13,"column":20,"offset":1243},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1,"offset":1224},"end":{"line":13,"column":20,"offset":1243},"indent":[]},"data":{"id":"oaks-conception","htmlAttributes":{"id":"oaks-conception"},"hProperties":{"id":"oaks-conception","style":"position:relative;"}}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Then, I had an idea. What if I kept the tape memory structure from Brain****, kept the memory management operations from free, and added some operators for managing a stack? The result was Oak’s backend assembly language. After a week of experimenting, I created an incredibly reduced instruction set with only 12 operators that could output basic C code. ","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1,"offset":1245},"end":{"line":15,"column":357,"offset":1601},"indent":[]}},{"type":"emphasis","children":[{"type":"text","value":"“This is perfect”","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":358,"offset":1602},"end":{"line":15,"column":375,"offset":1619},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":357,"offset":1601},"end":{"line":15,"column":376,"offset":1620},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":", I thought. I implemented an intermediate representation that implemented functions, structures, a type system, and basic operations that any programming language needs. I even added a foreign function interface, so that users could import C code into their programs! I was incredibly excited.","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":376,"offset":1620},"end":{"line":15,"column":670,"offset":1914},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1,"offset":1245},"end":{"line":15,"column":670,"offset":1914},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"image","title":null,"url":"/blog/media/oak.png","alt":"Oak Code","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1,"offset":1916},"end":{"line":17,"column":33,"offset":1948},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1,"offset":1916},"end":{"line":17,"column":33,"offset":1948},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"It was at about this point that the language took* off on Reddit, HackerNews, and GitHub. Only a ","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1,"offset":1950},"end":{"line":19,"column":98,"offset":2047},"indent":[]}},{"type":"emphasis","children":[{"type":"text","value":"single day","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":99,"offset":2048},"end":{"line":19,"column":109,"offset":2058},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":98,"offset":2047},"end":{"line":19,"column":110,"offset":2059},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" after posting the GitHub link to Reddit, I had over ","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":110,"offset":2059},"end":{"line":19,"column":163,"offset":2112},"indent":[]}},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"emphasis","children":[{"type":"text","value":"16,000","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":166,"offset":2115},"end":{"line":19,"column":172,"offset":2121},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":165,"offset":2114},"end":{"line":19,"column":173,"offset":2122},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":163,"offset":2112},"end":{"line":19,"column":175,"offset":2124},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" unique visitors to the repository. I had never received much attention on Reddit or GitHub, so this was incredibly powerful to me. It fueled me to keep going.","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":175,"offset":2124},"end":{"line":19,"column":334,"offset":2283},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1,"offset":1950},"end":{"line":19,"column":334,"offset":2283},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"At around this point, the project was still pretty barebones. It had all the basic necessities, but nothing more. There was still a ","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1,"offset":2285},"end":{"line":21,"column":133,"offset":2417},"indent":[]}},{"type":"emphasis","children":[{"type":"text","value":"lot","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":134,"offset":2418},"end":{"line":21,"column":137,"offset":2421},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":133,"offset":2417},"end":{"line":21,"column":138,"offset":2422},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" to be done. Oak was basically just a glorified, stripped down, and less robust C compiler.","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":138,"offset":2422},"end":{"line":21,"column":229,"offset":2513},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1,"offset":2285},"end":{"line":21,"column":229,"offset":2513},"indent":[]}},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"children":[{